### 3. Additional Improvements

#### a. Use Enum for States
Consider using an enum to represent the different states instead of relying solely on state objects. This can make it easier to manage and understand the current state.

#### b. Optimize State Logic
If you have more states, consider creating a base class for common functionality or using interfaces to define the behavior of states. This will help reduce redundancy.

