```javascript
if (!asset.downloaded) {
  console.error("Asset not downloaded");
  return; // Exit if not downloaded
}
```

### Conclusion

By following these steps, you should be able to identify the root cause of why the `copyAsync` function is not executing as expected. If the asset is not downloading correctly, focus on ensuring that the asset is accessible and correctly configured in your project.

